# Follow STYLE.md

When editing or adding UI, layout, or styles in this project, follow the conventions in **STYLE.md** at the project root.

## Must follow

- **Colors**: Use semantic tokens only (`text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `border-border`, `text-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, etc.). No raw hex/OKLCH in components.
- **Components**: Use shadcn/ui from `@/components/ui/*` (Button, Card, Input, Skeleton). Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for class merging.
- **Typography**: Geist Sans (`font-sans`), `antialiased` on body; headings use `font-semibold` or `font-medium` with `tracking-tight`.
- **Layout**: Root wrapper `min-h-screen bg-background font-sans`; main content `mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-12`; card padding `py-6` / `px-6`.
- **Theme**: Dark mode by default; globals and tokens live in `app/globals.css` with `@theme` and CSS variables.
- **Accessibility**: `focus-visible:` for focus styles; `aria-label` on icon-only buttons; `aria-invalid` where appropriate.
- **Icons**: Use Lordicon for all icons. Use `Player` from `@lordicon/react` with icon JSON; use `size`, `colorize`/`colors` for theming, and ref methods for animation.

Refer to **STYLE.md** for full token tables, component variants, spacing, and product-specific patterns.
